claim.claim-text:
1. A software as service method for distributing a digital representation of a cinematic production comprising the steps of:
a. a studio producing a digital source master (DSM) of the cinematic production on a non-transitory computer readable storage medium;
b. the studio distributing the DSM to at least one distributor;
c. the distributor producing a digital cinema distribution master (DCDM) from the DSM;
d. the distributor compressing the DCDM to a digital cinema package (DCP);
e. the distributor producing a key delivery message (KDM) unique to each DCP and cinema in the distributor's distribution chain;
f. selecting the cinematic production represented by the DCP from a list of cinematic productions;
g. selecting a priority type associated with delivery of the selected DCP;
h. identifying a transfer begin and end time of the selected DCP;
i. booking electronic delivery of the DCP to the cinema based upon the priority type selected, transfer time required, the transfer begin/end time;
j. booking electronic delivery of the DCP based also upon the priority type selected, transfer time required, the transfer begin/end time of a competing transfer to the same cinema; and
k. electronically delivering the DCP and KDM to the cinema.
